Which was exactly the calculation we had to make in the last band I as in.

We got offered a record deal but it wouldn't work unless we actually got
paid what we earned.

This meant a reasonable corporate set-up where the record royalties ,
especially the 'mechanical royalty' went to us rather than sitting in a
record company bank account for a couple of decades.

However,  on mentioning the words 'mechanical royalty' and  'band
incorporating itself as a limited company' to the record company we found
the deal evaporated.

Well,  not so much evaporated as disappeared in a cloud of dust and small
pebbles as the record company accountant's silver BMW Series 3 accelerated
down the path away from the cottage where we used to rehearse...

We went back to the £25,000 a year day jobs...

I'd probably have a go now as I'm retired,  but I'm also a bit old to go
touring these days...

--
William Black

