Pop music - since the 1920s at least - has always been about youth, good
looks, sex appeal, fashion - the 'cool' new look, the new 'in' sounds, the
new musical gimmick etc.  It is normal for teenagers to be a bit rebellious
and to reject their parent's tastes and go for something new and 'cool'.

But apart from that, the potential profit in the old days for selling a
million vinyl 45s in an exploitative contract deal kept it all going until
now.  The 'music biz' is shrinking 10% year on year.

Expect more and more copyright tightening backlash as they fight back in
sheer desperation.  I wish there was more youth-orientated music-making and
music sales to keep the biz profitable. It would impact less on me than it
does now - or is going to.

